Note: vulnerable/unsafe if paths come from untrusted input.
As written, the CLI blindly uses argv["docx-path"], output-path, output_dir, and style_map. If those are supplied by an external caller (not the local user), they can point anywhere on disk, causing reads/writes outside the intended workspace. Thatâ€™s classic path traversal when user input is not confined to a base.
